          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why do people relapse after rehab?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Many relapse after rehab because the transition from a highly controlled, deeply supportive environment back to normal daily life is intensely overwhelming. Without continued outpatient support and solid relapse prevention planning, old stressors quickly return."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is relapse a normal part of recovery?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. While it is not a requirement, statistics show a high percentage of individuals managing addiction will experience at least one relapse. It should be treated as a clinical sign to tweak the recovery program and get more support, rather than a moral failure."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why do people relapse on drugs specifically?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
